-- CVS forecasts 1st-quarter, 2008 earnings
-- 
-- Thu Jan 31, 2008 9:36am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/31/us-cvs-outlook-idUSWEN369220080131

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - CVS Caremark Corp ( CVS.N ) on Thursday forecast 2008 adjusted earnings of $2.43 to $2.50 per share and net earnings of $2.26 to $2.33 per share. 

 Analysts, on average, expect $2.32 per share excluding one-time items, according to Reuters Estimates. For the first quarter, CVS forecast adjusted earnings of 53 cents to 55 cents per share, and net earnings of 49 cents to 51 cents per share. Analysts expect 54 cents per share excluding one-time items. The company made the comments on a conference call with analysts. (Reporting by  Nicole Maestri ; editing by John Wallace)